Mkango Resources has announced the results of the DFS for the Songwe Hill Rare Earths Project in Malawi. The DFS indicates a US$559.0 million post-tax NPV, using a 10% nominal discount rate, and 31.5% post-tax IRR for 100% of Songwe. The DFS is based on Songwe as a stand-alone project selling MREC as opposed to separated rare earth oxides and excludes Pulawy, which has potential to add significant downstream value. Mkango & #HyProMag pleased to be part of of this ‚Ç¨14m project to strengthen #RareEarths supply chains ‚Äì also great to see site for #HyProMag Germany scale up in Pforzheim ‚Äì with Songwe DFS announced this week, Mkango can deliver a unique Mine ‚öíÔ∏èRefine üß™Recycle ‚ôªÔ∏è solution #MKA https://t.co/z8HPuGTWen The financial analysis doesn‚Äôt reflect any changes to the fiscal regime that may be contained in the MDA that is currently being negotiated with the Government of Malawi. The Company plans to announce the results of the feasibility study for an integrated project comprising both Songwe and Pulawy when both the MDA is completed for Songwe, and the feasibility study is completed for Pulawy. With the release of the Songwe DFS and in anticipation of releasing the Integrated DFS, Mkango continues to advance ongoing discussions with potential strategic investors, development and commercial banks, and off-takers, working closely with its brokers, its project finance advisors, Terrafranca Capital Partners, its United States strategic advisors, Jones Group International and EIT RawMaterials within the framework of the European Raw Materials Alliance. During the week of 27th June 2022, the company hosted site visits to Songwe for a number of major commercial and development banks. Derek Linfield, Chairman of Mkango, stated: ‚ÄúThis is a major milestone which few rare earth companies have been able to reach. It reflects the perseverance and outstanding work completed by our executive and management team since Project inception in 2010, as well as by o